$interpreted: Ralph: So you're hiding in the filthy Slums, are you, member of the Feather Clan? I'll find you no matter where you hide.
Ralph: I remember...must first infuse rune magic like this...
Hyacinthus: Eve...will she be alright?
Nigel: What's that noise? Are the nobles' men here to get Eve?
Nigel: Eve, I'll be right back. Cin, take care of Eve for me!
Hyacinthus: Eve, please tell me you'll be fine...
Hyacinthus: Who are you!?
Aosta: Member of the Feather Clan, is that her?
Hyacinthus: Are you here to harm Eve...get out!
Eve: Who are you?
Eve: Don't come near me...ugh!
Eve: You're...healing me? But, why... ?
Aosta: As a member of the precious Feather Clan, you don't have the right to die.
Aosta: Oh, so you're not dead yet.
Ralph: Bastard, you tampered with the stone shards!
Aosta: Using that thing is quite the delicate matter. Infuse the Soul Energy incorrectly, it leaks instantly;
Aosta: Infuse too much, it will explode...looks like you just experienced it first-hand?
Ralph: Whatever, still found the Feather Clan. No need for your useless toys...now die!
Ralph: ...Damnit!
Aosta: What is your purpose? Why do you insist on killing this girl?
Ralph: At least we can confirm one target...I'll let her go this time.
Aosta: Can't do anything about that. Shall we continue the treatment?
Eve: That person...what does he want to do to me?
Aosta: I don't know. However, what I do know is that your identity will attract more danger. People around you will be affected as well.
Eve: Does that include...people I care about?
Aosta: Yes.
Eve: I don't want...something like that to happen.
Aosta: That depends on the decision you make.
